      • createBucket

        public scala.concurrent.Future<Result<S3Metadata,Bucket>> createBucket(java.lang.String bucketname,
                                                              java.lang.String acls,
                                                              java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> permissions)
        Create a bucket Anonymous requests are never allowed to create buckets. By creating the bucket, you become the bucket owner. Not every string is an acceptable bucket name.
        Parameters:
        bucketname - The name of the bucket you want to create.
        acls - predefined grants for this Bucket
        permissions - Explicit access permissions
        region - Physical location of the bucket
        See Also:
        http://docs.amazonwebservices.com/AmazonS3/2006-03-01/dev/index.html?UsingBucket.html

      • listBuckets

        public scala.concurrent.Future<Result<S3Metadata,java.util.List<Bucket>>> listBuckets()
        Returns a list of all buckets owned by the authenticated sender of the request. Anonymous users cannot list buckets, and you cannot list buckets that you did not create.
